'''普若佛'''（{{lang-en|Provo}}）位於[[美国|美国]][[犹他州|犹他州]]，是该州第四大城市。该市在[[盐湖城|盐湖城]]南约{{convert|43|mi|km}} 处，是大都会区[[瓦萨其前线|瓦萨其前线]]的一部分。同时该市也是犹他县的县治及最大城市，美国高等学府[[杨百翰大学|杨百翰大学]]就位于此。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://vacationidea.com/destinations/best-things-to-do-in-provo-ut.html#:~:text=Located%2045%20miles%20south%20of,play%20in%20the%20United%20States. |title=25 Fun Things to Do in Provo, Utah |website=VacationIdea.com |date=2021-08-14 |access-date=2021-08-24 |archive-date=2021-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206052346/https://vacationidea.com/destinations/best-things-to-do-in-provo-ut.html#:~:text=Located%2045%20miles%20south%20of,play%20in%20the%20United%20States. |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==简介==
普若佛位于[[奥勒姆_(犹他州)|奥勒姆]]和[[斯普林维尔_(犹他州)|斯普林维尔]]之间。根据[[2020年美國人口普查|2020年的普查]]结果，该市共有115162人。<ref name = "provopopulation" />普若佛是[[普羅沃-奧勒姆都會區|普羅沃-奧勒姆都會區]]的主要城市，该都会区在[[2010年美國人口普查|2010年人口普查]]中有526810人，<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |title=2010 Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171) Summary File |work=2010 Census |publisher=[[United_States_Census_Bureau|United States Census Bureau]], Population Division |access-date=2011-02-05 |archive-date=1996-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19961227012639/http://www.census.gov/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>是犹他州仅次于[[鹽湖城都市區|鹽湖城都市區]]的第二大都市区。

普若佛是美国私立大学[[杨百翰大学|杨百翰大学]]的所在地，由[[耶稣基督后期圣徒教会|耶稣基督后期圣徒教会]]负责运转。普若佛还拥有耶稣基督后期圣徒教会最大的[[傳教士_(耶穌基督後期聖徒教會)|传教士]]训练中心。这座城市是犹他州技术发展的重点地区，拥有总市值数十亿美元的[[初创企业|初创企业]]。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pando.com/2013/07/25/the-street-in-provo-thats-home-to-three-billion-dollar-companies/|title=The street in Provo that's home to three billion-dollar tech companies|website=Pando|date=2013-07-25|access-date=2016-04-01|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417140027/https://pando.com/2013/07/25/the-street-in-provo-thats-home-to-three-billion-dollar-companies/|dead-url=no}}</ref>这座城市的山峰冰场是[[2002年冬季奥林匹克运动会|2002年盐湖城冬季奥运会]]的比赛场地，[[日舞渡假村|日舞渡假村]]位于普罗沃峡谷东北方向{{convert|13|mi}}处。

2015年，《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》将普若佛列为“最适合就业的中小城市”之一，<ref>{{cite magazine| title=The Best Small And Medium-Size Cities For Jobs 2015| magazine=Forbes| url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/joelkotkin/2015/06/12/best-small-and-medium-size-cities-for-jobs-2015/| access-date=2021-12-06| archive-date=2021-12-06| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206112902/https://www.forbes.com/sites/joelkotkin/2015/06/12/best-small-and-medium-size-cities-for-jobs-2015/| dead-url=no}}</ref>美国劳工统计局发现普若佛是犹他州2015年就业率增长最快的城市。<ref>{{cite web | title=Utah County, Utah, has largest over-the-year percent gain in employment, June 2015 | publisher=US Bureau of Labor Statistics | url=http://www.bls.gov/opub/ted/2015/utah-county-utah-has-largest-over-the-year-percent-gain-in-employment-june-2015.htm | date=2015-12-28 | access-date=2021-12-06 | archive-date=2021-12-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206112931/https://www.bls.gov/opub/ted/2015/utah-county-utah-has-largest-over-the-year-percent-gain-in-employment-june-2015.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>2013年，《福布斯》将普罗沃列为全球第二大最适合经商和就业的城市。<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Best Places For Business and Careers - Forbes|url=https://www.forbes.com/best-places-for-business/|magazine=Forbes|access-date=2014-01-13|archive-date=2013-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808004953/http://www.forbes.com/best-places-for-business|dead-url=no}}</ref>普罗沃在社会乐观（2012年）<ref>{{Cite news |title=Provo-Orem, Utah, Leads U.S. Metro Areas in City Optimism |date=March 2012 |url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/153206/Provo-Orem-Utah-Leads-Metro-Areas-City-Optimism.aspx |work=Gallup |access-date=2014-02-12 |archive-date=2017-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701002111/http://www.gallup.com/poll/153206/provo-orem-utah-leads-metro-areas-city-optimism.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>和健康/福祉（2014年）方面排名全球第一。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/167984/provo-orem-utah-leads-communities.aspx |title=Provo-Orem, Utah, Leads U.S. Communities in Well-Being |website=Gallup.com |date=2014-03-25 |access-date=2014-04-14 |archive-date=2017-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525211735/http://www.gallup.com/poll/167984/provo-orem-utah-leads-communities.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==历史==
[[File:Fort_Utah_c1850.jpg|thumb]]
普若佛最初叫“廷帕諾戈斯”，来源于犹特语，意思可能是“岩石河”。<ref name="Bright2004">{{cite book|last=Bright|first=William|author-link=William Bright|title=Native American Placenames of the United States|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5XfxzCm1qa4C&pg=PA495|access-date=2019-02-10|year=2004|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|isbn=978-0-8061-3598-4|page=495|archive-date=2021-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206092513/https://books.google.com/books?id=5XfxzCm1qa4C&pg=PA495|dead-url=no}}</ref>该地区居住着廷帕諾戈斯人。<ref name=historytogo5 />现在这里是犹他州人口最多的地区之一。<ref name=Virginia >{{cite book|title=Ute Indians of Utah, Colorado, and New Mexico|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dMS9AwAAQBAJ&q=%22Utah+lake%22+among+Ute&pg=PT32|author=Virginia McConnell Simmons|date=2011-05-18|isbn=9781457109898|access-date=2021-12-06|archive-date=2021-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206092744/https://books.google.com/books?id=dMS9AwAAQBAJ&q=%22Utah+lake%22+among+Ute&pg=PT32|dead-url=no}}</ref>来自普若佛河的充足食物使廷帕诺戈斯人成为爱好和平的民族。<ref name=historytogo5>{{cite web|url=http://historytogo.utah.gov/people/ethnic_cultures/the_history_of_utahs_american_indians/chapter5.html|title=Chapter Five - The Northern Utes of Utah|access-date=2016-07-25|archive-date=2016-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508235935/http://historytogo.utah.gov/people/ethnic_cultures/the_history_of_utahs_american_indians/chapter5.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>该地区也是尤特族和休休尼族传统的聚会场所，同时也是这些民族的宗教圣地。<ref name=blackhawk>{{cite book|title=Indian Depredations in Utah|url=http://www.blackhawkwarutah.com/|author=Peter Gottfredson|access-date=2018-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121184357/http://www.blackhawkwarutah.com/|archive-date=2018-01-21|url-status=dead}}</ref>

第一个到访该地的欧洲探险家是西班牙[[方济各会|方济各会]]的传教士西尔维斯特·贝莱斯·德·埃斯卡兰特神父，他于1776年在两个犹特人向导的带领下访问了这里，他还给这两个向导分别取名为“荒野”和“华金”。<ref name=Joaquin>{{cite web|url=http://www.provo.org/Home/ShowDocument?id=2258|title=Joaquin Neighborhood Plan pg. 3 :: City of Provo|access-date=2021-12-06|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225000113/http://www.provo.org/Home/ShowDocument?id=2258|dead-url=no}}</ref>埃斯卡兰特记录了欧洲人第一次穿越[[大盆地沙漠|大盆地沙漠]]的探险。这些欧洲人并没有建立永久定居点，而是选择与原住民进行商业贸易。<ref name=Virginia />

